WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.050 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.050 --> 00:00:11.400 align:middle line:90%
>> My name's Patrick Holdford.

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:13.830 align:middle line:84%
I started out as a
psychologist, and I

00:00:13.830 --> 00:00:17.940 align:middle line:84%
was fascinated in what goes
wrong in severe mental illness,

00:00:17.940 --> 00:00:19.590 align:middle line:90%
schizophrenia.

00:00:19.590 --> 00:00:23.340 align:middle line:84%
And way back in the '70s,
I came across this research

00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:27.060 align:middle line:84%
that was reporting
incredible results using

00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:28.740 align:middle line:90%
very large amounts of vitamins.

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:33.670 align:middle line:84%
Not psychotherapy, not
drugs, but actually vitamins.

00:00:33.670 --> 00:00:36.060 align:middle line:84%
And this was really
good research.

00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:37.923 align:middle line:84%
I took it's my professor
and he said, ah,

00:00:37.923 --> 00:00:39.690 align:middle line:90%
it's a load of nonsense.

00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:41.580 align:middle line:90%
But I couldn't really fault it.

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:44.790 align:middle line:84%
So I jumped on a plane,
and I went to North America

00:00:44.790 --> 00:00:47.370 align:middle line:84%
to meet the people
who'd done the research.

00:00:47.370 --> 00:00:50.000 align:middle line:84%
This man called
Dr. Abram Hoffer.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:54.655 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what is your
success rate using nutrition

00:00:54.655 --> 00:00:55.455 align:middle line:90%
for schizophrenia?

00:00:55.455 --> 00:00:58.800 align:middle line:90%
And he said 85% cure.

00:00:58.800 --> 00:01:02.130 align:middle line:84%
Now, I nearly fell off my chair,
because most psychiatrists

00:01:02.130 --> 00:01:06.780 align:middle line:84%
have never seen anyone
with schizophrenia cured.

00:01:06.780 --> 00:01:09.060 align:middle line:84%
I said, what's your
definition of cure?

00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:11.880 align:middle line:84%
He said, free of symptoms,
able to socialize

00:01:11.880 --> 00:01:15.630 align:middle line:84%
with family and friends,
and paying income tax.

00:01:15.630 --> 00:01:17.190 align:middle line:90%
And thus, I became his student.

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:20.550 align:middle line:84%
And I have seen hundreds
of people diagnosed

00:01:20.550 --> 00:01:24.090 align:middle line:84%
with schizophrenia,
severe mental illness, who

00:01:24.090 --> 00:01:27.220 align:middle line:90%
don't have it anymore.

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.750 align:middle line:84%
One of the brightest
minds in science

00:01:30.750 --> 00:01:34.710 align:middle line:84%
in the last century or two,
Dr. Linus Pauling, Einstein's

00:01:34.710 --> 00:01:37.800 align:middle line:84%
friend, found out
about this research

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:40.680 align:middle line:84%
using very large
amounts of vitamin C

00:01:40.680 --> 00:01:44.580 align:middle line:84%
and niacin, some B
vitamin folic acid.

00:01:44.580 --> 00:01:47.430 align:middle line:84%
And he also had
never seen a chemical

00:01:47.430 --> 00:01:49.380 align:middle line:84%
where tiny amount,
and we're talking

00:01:49.380 --> 00:01:53.390 align:middle line:84%
10 milligrams of vitamin C,
less than you can barely see,

00:01:53.390 --> 00:01:55.950 align:middle line:90%
will stop you dying from scurvy.

00:01:55.950 --> 00:01:59.230 align:middle line:84%
And yet, massive amounts,
like 10,000 milligrams,

00:01:59.230 --> 00:02:02.710 align:middle line:84%
which is completely non-toxic,
can have these profound health

00:02:02.710 --> 00:02:03.510 align:middle line:90%
benefits.

00:02:03.510 --> 00:02:08.100 align:middle line:84%
Not only antipsychotic,
but anti cancer, antiviral.

00:02:08.100 --> 00:02:13.040 align:middle line:84%
So he started to really
focus on this whole area.

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:17.190 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is a man with two
Nobel prizes and 48 PhDs.

00:02:17.190 --> 00:02:18.720 align:middle line:90%
He's very, very bright.

00:02:18.720 --> 00:02:23.100 align:middle line:84%
All of modern biochemistry is
really based upon his work.

00:02:23.100 --> 00:02:26.010 align:middle line:84%
And very soon, he realized
that the future of medicine--

00:02:26.010 --> 00:02:29.280 align:middle line:84%
if I quote him-- the future of
medicine is optimum nutrition.

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:32.130 align:middle line:84%
Optimum nutrition is the
medicine of tomorrow.

00:02:32.130 --> 00:02:35.363 align:middle line:84%
If you have any disease for
which you go to your doctor

00:02:35.363 --> 00:02:36.780 align:middle line:84%
and they've
prescribed you a drug,

00:02:36.780 --> 00:02:40.140 align:middle line:84%
it means that the drug only
works because your chemistry is

00:02:40.140 --> 00:02:41.820 align:middle line:90%
out of balance.

00:02:41.820 --> 00:02:47.100 align:middle line:84%
And what we're saying is
that if you can find out

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:51.310 align:middle line:84%
what is your perfect
intake of the nutrients,

00:02:51.310 --> 00:02:54.320 align:middle line:84%
these are the chemicals that
are part of our evolution,

00:02:54.320 --> 00:02:56.760 align:middle line:84%
they're part of how
we are designed,

00:02:56.760 --> 00:02:59.550 align:middle line:84%
and you can take them in
through diet and supplements,

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:03.030 align:middle line:84%
they will bring your
out of balance system

00:03:03.030 --> 00:03:06.480 align:middle line:84%
back into balance
and restore health.

00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:10.770 align:middle line:84%
And we've literally spent
the last 20 years exploring

00:03:10.770 --> 00:03:15.030 align:middle line:84%
exactly what you need to
do, what you need to eat,

00:03:15.030 --> 00:03:17.850 align:middle line:84%
to be in the best
possible health.

00:03:17.850 --> 00:03:21.180 align:middle line:84%
Most of us are quite literally
digging our own graves

00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:22.950 align:middle line:90%
with a knife and fork.

00:03:22.950 --> 00:03:26.040 align:middle line:84%
And when you get your own
optimum nutrition right--

00:03:26.040 --> 00:03:28.350 align:middle line:84%
and it's really not
that difficult--

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:30.030 align:middle line:84%
you're not only
going to add probably

00:03:30.030 --> 00:03:36.820 align:middle line:84%
10 years to your healthy life
but also life to your years.

00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:43.980 align:middle line:84%
Did you know that obesity is the
second most preventable cause

00:03:43.980 --> 00:03:46.380 align:middle line:90%
of death?

00:03:46.380 --> 00:03:49.860 align:middle line:90%
Smoking being the first.

00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:51.950 align:middle line:90%
Obesity is widespread.

00:03:51.950 --> 00:03:53.910 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's a joke
in more ways than one.

00:03:53.910 --> 00:03:58.500 align:middle line:84%
But it's not a joke, because
there is this whole trend now

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:02.650 align:middle line:84%
that so many of us are gaining
weight and then becoming obese,

00:04:02.650 --> 00:04:04.710 align:middle line:90%
which is extreme overweight.

00:04:04.710 --> 00:04:08.230 align:middle line:84%
And this is leading into so
many other diseases-- diabetes,

00:04:08.230 --> 00:04:11.260 align:middle line:84%
heart disease,
depression, and so on.

00:04:11.260 --> 00:04:13.380 align:middle line:84%
So the real question
is why and how

00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:15.900 align:middle line:90%
can you reverse this process?

00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:17.790 align:middle line:84%
Now, I'm going to
tell you something

00:04:17.790 --> 00:04:19.890 align:middle line:90%
that might surprise you.

00:04:19.890 --> 00:04:25.650 align:middle line:84%
It's not about calories,
and it's not about fat.

00:04:25.650 --> 00:04:30.060 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the statistics,
for example, in Britain,

00:04:30.060 --> 00:04:33.780 align:middle line:84%
we have started over
the last 15 years

00:04:33.780 --> 00:04:38.220 align:middle line:84%
to consume less calories
and much less fat.

00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:41.400 align:middle line:84%
In America, they've cut
the percentage of calories

00:04:41.400 --> 00:04:45.632 align:middle line:90%
from fat from 42% to 34%.

00:04:45.632 --> 00:04:49.380 align:middle line:84%
And what difference has it
made to the obesity epidemic?

00:04:49.380 --> 00:04:50.250 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:04:50.250 --> 00:04:53.520 align:middle line:90%
It continues, ever-growing.

00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:56.820 align:middle line:84%
The real problem with
obesity and weight gain

00:04:56.820 --> 00:05:00.360 align:middle line:84%
has to do with your
blood sugar level.

00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:02.520 align:middle line:84%
Put very simply,
we run on glucose.

00:05:02.520 --> 00:05:05.640 align:middle line:84%
We don't run on calories,
we run on glucose.

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:08.550 align:middle line:84%
And when your blood
sugar level is too high,

00:05:08.550 --> 00:05:10.740 align:middle line:90%
you dump the excess as fat.

00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:14.430 align:middle line:84%
And when your blood sugar level
is too low, you get hungry,

00:05:14.430 --> 00:05:16.380 align:middle line:90%
and you get tired.

00:05:16.380 --> 00:05:20.250 align:middle line:84%
The first guy who caught onto
this was Atkins, Dr. Atkins.

00:05:20.250 --> 00:05:25.170 align:middle line:84%
He realized that protein and fat
don't affect your blood sugar.

00:05:25.170 --> 00:05:26.490 align:middle line:90%
So he said, OK.

00:05:26.490 --> 00:05:28.750 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to give
people a diet of protein

00:05:28.750 --> 00:05:31.320 align:middle line:90%
and fat, no carbohydrate.

00:05:31.320 --> 00:05:35.070 align:middle line:84%
And sure enough, their hunger
reduced, and it worked.

00:05:35.070 --> 00:05:36.800 align:middle line:90%
They lost weight.

00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:38.940 align:middle line:84%
And it does work
for weight loss.

00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:41.790 align:middle line:84%
But that kind of diet
really isn't good for you

00:05:41.790 --> 00:05:42.590 align:middle line:90%
in the long run.

00:05:42.590 --> 00:05:45.780 align:middle line:84%
And even if the idea of
bacon and eggs for breakfast

00:05:45.780 --> 00:05:48.510 align:middle line:84%
fills you with great glee
as a way to lose weight,

00:05:48.510 --> 00:05:50.970 align:middle line:84%
it probably won't
in two months time,

00:05:50.970 --> 00:05:56.260 align:middle line:84%
because we crave foods like
bread, pasta, and so on.

00:05:56.260 --> 00:06:00.520 align:middle line:84%
So the real answer
to losing weight,

00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:04.240 align:middle line:84%
of reversing this process, is
to balance your blood sugar.

00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:08.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's done by eating what's
called a low glycemic load

00:06:08.140 --> 00:06:10.840 align:middle line:90%
diet, or GL diet.

00:06:10.840 --> 00:06:14.620 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to be as extreme
as the Atkins type approach.

00:06:14.620 --> 00:06:16.990 align:middle line:90%
Yes, you need some protein.

00:06:16.990 --> 00:06:19.800 align:middle line:84%
And yes, you also need what
we call the slow releasing

00:06:19.800 --> 00:06:20.710 align:middle line:90%
carbohydrates.

00:06:20.710 --> 00:06:23.530 align:middle line:90%
That's the low GI foods.

00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:27.160 align:middle line:84%
An example would be an oat
based cereal for breakfast

00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:31.300 align:middle line:84%
rather than cornflakes, or
eating barriers or an apple

00:06:31.300 --> 00:06:35.690 align:middle line:84%
rather than eating
a banana or raisins.

00:06:35.690 --> 00:06:41.530 align:middle line:84%
So if you learn how to combine
the right kind of proteins

00:06:41.530 --> 00:06:44.620 align:middle line:84%
with these slow
releasing carbohydrates,

00:06:44.620 --> 00:06:48.340 align:middle line:84%
and actually eating more food,
having breakfast, lunch, dinner

00:06:48.340 --> 00:06:52.340 align:middle line:84%
and two snacks, as long as
you get your blood sugar

00:06:52.340 --> 00:06:56.890 align:middle line:84%
effect right, you'll feel
full, you won't get hungry,

00:06:56.890 --> 00:06:59.800 align:middle line:84%
your craving for sweet
foods will reduce,

00:06:59.800 --> 00:07:01.990 align:middle line:90%
and so will your weight.

00:07:01.990 --> 00:07:03.670 align:middle line:84%
We've done a lot of
research on this,

00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:09.020 align:middle line:84%
and consistently, we find people
losing substantial amounts.

00:07:09.020 --> 00:07:14.290 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking about six to
12 kilos in six weeks.

00:07:14.290 --> 00:07:19.000 align:middle line:84%
But what's amazing is as people
find their weight leaving,

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:20.840 align:middle line:90%
they feel so fantastic.

00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:24.790 align:middle line:84%
So if the idea of losing
weight, feeling great,

00:07:24.790 --> 00:07:28.420 align:middle line:84%
not feeling hungry,
never feeling hungry,

00:07:28.420 --> 00:07:33.310 align:middle line:84%
and losing your desire for
very sweet foods attracts you,

00:07:33.310 --> 00:07:38.020 align:middle line:84%
then you need to learn how to
eat a low glycemic low diet,

00:07:38.020 --> 00:07:39.250 align:middle line:90%
a low GL diet.

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:43.870 align:middle line:84%
That is the future of
all weight control.

00:07:43.870 --> 00:07:47.920 align:middle line:84%
So you might have heard
of GI, or Glycemic Index.

00:07:47.920 --> 00:07:50.170 align:middle line:90%
It's a very useful measure.

00:07:50.170 --> 00:07:54.010 align:middle line:84%
It's a measure out of 100,
and if a food has a high GI,

00:07:54.010 --> 00:07:56.345 align:middle line:84%
it means the sugar in
it releases quickly

00:07:56.345 --> 00:07:57.220 align:middle line:90%
into the bloodstream.

00:07:57.220 --> 00:08:01.700 align:middle line:84%
Cornflakes would be an example,
while oat flakes has a low GI.

00:08:01.700 --> 00:08:04.930 align:middle line:84%
So the general message is
if you eat low GI foods

00:08:04.930 --> 00:08:07.550 align:middle line:84%
like apple and
oats for breakfast,

00:08:07.550 --> 00:08:10.480 align:middle line:84%
it will make you feel fuller
for longer than eating something

00:08:10.480 --> 00:08:13.283 align:middle line:90%
like Cornflakes and raisins.

00:08:13.283 --> 00:08:14.575 align:middle line:90%
Take something like watermelon.

00:08:14.575 --> 00:08:17.300 align:middle line:90%
It has a score of 72.

00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:19.330 align:middle line:84%
So that means that the
sugar in watermelon

00:08:19.330 --> 00:08:21.910 align:middle line:90%
releases very, very fast.

00:08:21.910 --> 00:08:24.910 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's a problem with
GI, and watermelon's a good way

00:08:24.910 --> 00:08:26.680 align:middle line:90%
to illustrate.

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:29.110 align:middle line:84%
Number one, there
have been 12 diets

00:08:29.110 --> 00:08:32.380 align:middle line:84%
based on low GI
foods, five of which

00:08:32.380 --> 00:08:37.150 align:middle line:84%
have shown weight loss, four of
which have shown weight gain,

00:08:37.150 --> 00:08:39.530 align:middle line:84%
and three of which have
shown no different.

00:08:39.530 --> 00:08:43.240 align:middle line:84%
So even though these low GI
foods are very good for you,

00:08:43.240 --> 00:08:47.320 align:middle line:84%
the evidence of just eating
low GI foods to lose weight

00:08:47.320 --> 00:08:48.790 align:middle line:90%
is not great.

00:08:48.790 --> 00:08:50.380 align:middle line:90%
Now, watermelon.

00:08:50.380 --> 00:08:52.390 align:middle line:90%
Let's come back to that.

00:08:52.390 --> 00:08:54.850 align:middle line:84%
If you were thinking
like Atkins who

00:08:54.850 --> 00:08:59.050 align:middle line:84%
limited the amount of
carbohydrate in a food,

00:08:59.050 --> 00:09:01.120 align:middle line:84%
watermelons are a
very, very good food,

00:09:01.120 --> 00:09:04.450 align:middle line:84%
because it actually has very
little carbohydrate in it.

00:09:04.450 --> 00:09:10.190 align:middle line:84%
A nice, big 120 gram slice is
only six grams of carbohydrate.

00:09:10.190 --> 00:09:12.010 align:middle line:90%
So he'd say yeah, tick the box.

00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:14.710 align:middle line:90%
It's mainly water.

00:09:14.710 --> 00:09:17.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, but the kind of
carbohydrate in it,

00:09:17.260 --> 00:09:20.110 align:middle line:84%
the kind of sugar in it
is very fast releasing.

00:09:20.110 --> 00:09:22.810 align:middle line:90%
So it has a GI of 72.

00:09:22.810 --> 00:09:25.960 align:middle line:84%
And most books will tell
you above 70 is bad news.

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:28.420 align:middle line:90%
Never eat it.

00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:31.150 align:middle line:84%
So it's a bit
misleading, the GI.

00:09:31.150 --> 00:09:34.780 align:middle line:84%
Because you could eat a food
that has fast releasing sugar

00:09:34.780 --> 00:09:37.450 align:middle line:84%
but so little of
it, and actually

00:09:37.450 --> 00:09:40.750 align:middle line:84%
it really won't affect
your bloodstream much.

00:09:40.750 --> 00:09:43.010 align:middle line:84%
Or you could eat a
food like chocolate,

00:09:43.010 --> 00:09:46.640 align:middle line:84%
which has a GI of 49,
and most foods below 50,

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:48.830 align:middle line:90%
you're meant to eat them.

00:09:48.830 --> 00:09:52.360 align:middle line:84%
So the sugar in chocolate
actually releases more slowly

00:09:52.360 --> 00:09:53.260 align:middle line:90%
than watermelon.

00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:55.340 align:middle line:90%
But there's lots of it.

00:09:55.340 --> 00:09:57.760 align:middle line:90%
So the net effect is very bad.

00:09:57.760 --> 00:10:00.280 align:middle line:84%
So all the scientific
community now

00:10:00.280 --> 00:10:05.080 align:middle line:84%
have moved to something
called GL, or glycemic load,

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:07.450 align:middle line:84%
and that's when you
both take into account

00:10:07.450 --> 00:10:09.700 align:middle line:90%
what Atkins was about, i.e.

00:10:09.700 --> 00:10:13.210 align:middle line:84%
How much carbohydrate
there is in the food,

00:10:13.210 --> 00:10:18.670 align:middle line:84%
and you take into account how
fast the sugar in the food

00:10:18.670 --> 00:10:20.950 align:middle line:90%
actually releases.

00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And in the case of watermelon,
if you put these two together,

00:10:24.680 --> 00:10:28.010 align:middle line:84%
you get a GL of four,
which is very low.

00:10:28.010 --> 00:10:29.950 align:middle line:84%
So there's absolutely
nothing wrong

00:10:29.950 --> 00:10:32.860 align:middle line:84%
with eating a slice
of watermelon.

00:10:32.860 --> 00:10:36.730 align:middle line:84%
GL is the future, because
it's the only precise way

00:10:36.730 --> 00:10:40.360 align:middle line:84%
to know exactly what a food's
going to do to your energy,

00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:43.810 align:middle line:84%
to your blood sugar,
and your weight.

00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:45.790 align:middle line:84%
The World Health
Organization say

00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:50.110 align:middle line:84%
that the biggest problem
facing us in the 21st century

00:10:50.110 --> 00:10:51.370 align:middle line:90%
is not cancer.

00:10:51.370 --> 00:10:52.940 align:middle line:90%
It's not heart disease.

00:10:52.940 --> 00:10:55.390 align:middle line:90%
It's actually mental illness.

00:10:55.390 --> 00:11:01.420 align:middle line:84%
And of that depression,
is a major, major part.

00:11:01.420 --> 00:11:04.930 align:middle line:84%
In America, a staggering
one in nine women

00:11:04.930 --> 00:11:07.560 align:middle line:90%
are now taking antidepressants.

00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:11.530 align:middle line:84%
15% of the population in
most Western countries

00:11:11.530 --> 00:11:13.690 align:middle line:90%
are clinically depressed.

00:11:13.690 --> 00:11:15.940 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what is going on?

00:11:15.940 --> 00:11:18.760 align:middle line:90%
Yes, our world has changed.

00:11:18.760 --> 00:11:21.670 align:middle line:84%
We're under more
stress, more pressure.

00:11:21.670 --> 00:11:24.580 align:middle line:84%
The pace of change
is massive, and I'm

00:11:24.580 --> 00:11:28.240 align:middle line:84%
sure that's difficult
for many of us.

00:11:28.240 --> 00:11:31.720 align:middle line:84%
But what's extraordinary
is that the impact

00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:35.740 align:middle line:84%
of what you put in
your mouth on the brain

