00:13:41.965 --> 00:13:43.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm not ringing
for an interview.

00:13:43.340 --> 00:13:45.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm ringing to say thank you.

00:13:45.110 --> 00:13:47.420 align:middle line:84%
I've been depressed
for four months.

00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:50.810 align:middle line:84%
I followed your advice,
and it took 45 minutes

00:13:50.810 --> 00:13:53.330 align:middle line:90%
to come out of depression.

00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:59.330 align:middle line:84%
What you eat, B vitamins, omega
3, balancing your blood sugar,

00:13:59.330 --> 00:14:02.360 align:middle line:84%
exercise, getting
enough sunlight,

00:14:02.360 --> 00:14:04.940 align:middle line:84%
these are critical
factors that may

00:14:04.940 --> 00:14:08.900 align:middle line:84%
make you unable to deal with
the unavoidable stressors

00:14:08.900 --> 00:14:10.350 align:middle line:90%
in your life.

00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:14.750 align:middle line:84%
So you might not think about
it, but when your mood is low,

00:14:14.750 --> 00:14:19.580 align:middle line:84%
when you feel very anxious,
or your memory isn't great,

00:14:19.580 --> 00:14:22.010 align:middle line:84%
or you're not
sleeping, it may simply

00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:25.400 align:middle line:84%
be that you're not getting
the right nutrients that

00:14:25.400 --> 00:14:31.000 align:middle line:84%
allow your brain to
function properly.

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:34.633 align:middle line:84%
So maybe you've been diagnosed
with a health problem.

00:14:34.633 --> 00:14:36.050 align:middle line:84%
What are you going
to do about it?

00:14:36.050 --> 00:14:39.570 align:middle line:84%
Are you're going to freak
out and go to your doctor

00:14:39.570 --> 00:14:43.500 align:middle line:84%
and just follow
exactly what they say?

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:48.540 align:middle line:84%
Or are you going to really
take responsibility for this?

00:14:48.540 --> 00:14:53.940 align:middle line:84%
And responsibility means
responding, understanding

00:14:53.940 --> 00:14:59.310 align:middle line:84%
how it is that this happened
to your body, really learning.

00:14:59.310 --> 00:15:02.430 align:middle line:84%
Because every disease is
an incredible opportunity

00:15:02.430 --> 00:15:04.050 align:middle line:90%
to learn.

00:15:04.050 --> 00:15:08.820 align:middle line:84%
And you will find a wealth
of information to guide you.

00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:10.960 align:middle line:90%
There are tests that you can do.

00:15:10.960 --> 00:15:14.070 align:middle line:84%
And if your doctor runs tests,
make sure you get a copy.

00:15:14.070 --> 00:15:15.590 align:middle line:90%
Study these tests.

00:15:15.590 --> 00:15:19.380 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of practitioners
out there who can guide you.

00:15:19.380 --> 00:15:21.510 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the
day, the only person

00:15:21.510 --> 00:15:24.970 align:middle line:84%
who can help you,
really, truly is you.

00:15:24.970 --> 00:15:26.940 align:middle line:90%
You are your best physician.

00:15:26.940 --> 00:15:30.330 align:middle line:84%
So with the guidance of your
doctor, any information you

00:15:30.330 --> 00:15:34.260 align:middle line:84%
can get, other practitioners,
the important point

00:15:34.260 --> 00:15:37.690 align:middle line:84%
is that most diseases
are reversible.

00:15:37.690 --> 00:15:42.330 align:middle line:84%
It does take a change, because
the definition of insanity

00:15:42.330 --> 00:15:47.940 align:middle line:84%
is to keep doing the same things
and expect different results.

00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:51.120 align:middle line:84%
In truth, genes
don't cause disease.

00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:53.950 align:middle line:84%
But in the most case when
we're talking about cancer,

00:15:53.950 --> 00:15:56.970 align:middle line:84%
heart disease, diabetes,
and so on, what happens

00:15:56.970 --> 00:16:02.310 align:middle line:84%
is what you inherit is
instructions in your genes

00:16:02.310 --> 00:16:05.190 align:middle line:84%
that enable you to make
things in your body

00:16:05.190 --> 00:16:08.490 align:middle line:84%
like hormones,
enzymes, and so on.

00:16:08.490 --> 00:16:12.480 align:middle line:84%
So it's possible that you
may inherit the tendency

00:16:12.480 --> 00:16:16.020 align:middle line:84%
to diabetes, because
certain hormones that

00:16:16.020 --> 00:16:21.360 align:middle line:84%
keep your blood sugar stable are
more likely to work less well.

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:24.900 align:middle line:84%
But it's just literally
that, more likely.

00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:30.660 align:middle line:84%
Because genes are dependent
upon the environment

00:16:30.660 --> 00:16:32.760 align:middle line:90%
in which you've made the genes.

00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:36.150 align:middle line:84%
And that environment is
made by what you eat.

00:16:36.150 --> 00:16:39.600 align:middle line:84%
So when you change
your diet, you actually

00:16:39.600 --> 00:16:43.080 align:middle line:84%
change the expression
of your genes,

00:16:43.080 --> 00:16:47.190 align:middle line:84%
which ones are turned on, and
which ones are turned off.

00:16:47.190 --> 00:16:50.410 align:middle line:84%
So it's not really genes
that cause disease.

00:16:50.410 --> 00:16:54.150 align:middle line:84%
They just give you a
greater predisposition.

00:16:54.150 --> 00:16:58.020 align:middle line:84%
What causes disease
is the interaction

00:16:58.020 --> 00:17:03.240 align:middle line:84%
between what you've inherited,
your genes, and how you live.

00:17:03.240 --> 00:17:06.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, the bottom line
is, you can't change

00:17:06.390 --> 00:17:08.160 align:middle line:90%
the genes you've inherited.

00:17:08.160 --> 00:17:13.020 align:middle line:84%
But you can change how
you live and what you eat.

00:17:13.020 --> 00:17:16.410 align:middle line:84%
And when you change
those, even the diseases

00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:21.240 align:middle line:84%
that we think of as largely
genetic can be reversed.

00:17:21.240 --> 00:17:25.560 align:middle line:84%
So why not focus on changing
what you can rather than

00:17:25.560 --> 00:17:29.130 align:middle line:84%
talking about changing
what you can't?

00:17:29.130 --> 00:17:31.740 align:middle line:84%
You can get all the nutrients
you need from a well-balanced.

00:17:31.740 --> 00:17:35.470 align:middle line:84%
Diet do you believe
this statement?

00:17:35.470 --> 00:17:39.840 align:middle line:84%
It's the biggest lie
in nutrition today.

00:17:39.840 --> 00:17:44.040 align:middle line:84%
It has this notion that if
you eat a Harvest Festival

00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:46.850 align:middle line:84%
spread with your brown
bread and fruit and veg,

00:17:46.850 --> 00:17:48.660 align:middle line:90%
you get everything you need.

00:17:48.660 --> 00:17:51.197 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, if I stop someone
in the high street and say,

00:17:51.197 --> 00:17:52.530 align:middle line:90%
do you eat a well-balanced diet?

00:17:52.530 --> 00:17:54.030 align:middle line:90%
They'll say, well, yeah.

00:17:54.030 --> 00:17:56.380 align:middle line:90%
I think so.

00:17:56.380 --> 00:17:59.183 align:middle line:84%
And then you ask, well, what
is a well-balanced diet?

00:17:59.183 --> 00:18:00.600 align:middle line:84%
And you're told,
well, it's a diet

00:18:00.600 --> 00:18:02.490 align:middle line:90%
that gives you all you need.

00:18:02.490 --> 00:18:05.160 align:middle line:90%
And you go round and round.

00:18:05.160 --> 00:18:09.210 align:middle line:84%
In fact, some supposed
experts will tell you

00:18:09.210 --> 00:18:11.332 align:middle line:90%
that if you eat the RDA--

00:18:11.332 --> 00:18:13.290 align:middle line:84%
that's what you read on
the Cornflakes packet--

00:18:13.290 --> 00:18:17.310 align:middle line:84%
it stands for the Ridiculous
Dietary Arbitraries--

00:18:17.310 --> 00:18:19.170 align:middle line:90%
you get everything you need.

00:18:19.170 --> 00:18:21.330 align:middle line:84%
That if you get
your 60 milligrams

00:18:21.330 --> 00:18:23.820 align:middle line:90%
of vitamin C, no worries.

00:18:23.820 --> 00:18:24.970 align:middle line:90%
That's fine.

00:18:24.970 --> 00:18:30.370 align:middle line:84%
Anything more than that,
they say, is expensive urine.

00:18:30.370 --> 00:18:33.010 align:middle line:84%
But it's crazy, because
you and I are unique.

00:18:33.010 --> 00:18:34.330 align:middle line:90%
We're different.

00:18:34.330 --> 00:18:35.835 align:middle line:90%
We're physically different.

00:18:35.835 --> 00:18:37.920 align:middle line:90%
We're biochemically different.

00:18:37.920 --> 00:18:41.510 align:middle line:84%
And our need for nutrients
is definitely different.

00:18:41.510 --> 00:18:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And expecting you and I to have
the same need for vitamin C

00:18:45.690 --> 00:18:50.730 align:middle line:84%
is like expecting us
to need size 10 shoes.

00:18:50.730 --> 00:18:53.400 align:middle line:90%
It just doesn't work like that.

00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:57.120 align:middle line:84%
And what's becoming very, very
clear in the field of nutrition

00:18:57.120 --> 00:18:59.850 align:middle line:84%
is that if you are in
any disease process,

00:18:59.850 --> 00:19:05.670 align:middle line:84%
or maybe your energy is low,
you may need extra nutrients.

00:19:05.670 --> 00:19:08.920 align:middle line:84%
Yes, it's very important
to eat good food.

00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:11.670 align:middle line:84%
That's the cornerstone
of nutrition.

00:19:11.670 --> 00:19:15.730 align:middle line:84%
But you will find that there
are all sorts of vitamins,

00:19:15.730 --> 00:19:19.470 align:middle line:84%
minerals, and essential
fats, the intake of which,

00:19:19.470 --> 00:19:22.590 align:middle line:84%
through supplements, can
not only restore your health

00:19:22.590 --> 00:19:24.940 align:middle line:84%
but make you feel
much, much better.

00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:28.350 align:middle line:84%
So if you want to be
in average poor health,

00:19:28.350 --> 00:19:31.310 align:middle line:84%
eat an average,
well balanced diet.

00:19:31.310 --> 00:19:36.500 align:middle line:84%
But if what you want is to be
100% healthy, feeling great,

00:19:36.500 --> 00:19:39.140 align:middle line:84%
and stay free from
disease, then what you need

00:19:39.140 --> 00:19:40.850 align:middle line:90%
is optimum nutrition.

00:19:40.850 --> 00:19:44.730 align:middle line:84%
And that means a little more
than a well-balanced diet.

00:19:44.730 --> 00:19:47.630 align:middle line:84%
And personally, I'd
recommend that to that,

00:19:47.630 --> 00:19:51.510 align:middle line:90%
you add some decent supplements.

00:19:51.510 --> 00:19:54.710 align:middle line:84%
I want to tell you a story
of a man called Andy.

00:19:54.710 --> 00:19:56.780 align:middle line:84%
I went on television
recently and I

00:19:56.780 --> 00:19:59.400 align:middle line:84%
said, give me a man with
a high cholesterol level,

00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:01.390 align:middle line:90%
and give me three weeks.

00:20:01.390 --> 00:20:02.620 align:middle line:90%
And Andy rang up.

00:20:02.620 --> 00:20:04.750 align:middle line:84%
His cholesterol had
been very, very high,

00:20:04.750 --> 00:20:06.370 align:middle line:90%
and he'd been prescribed a drug.

00:20:06.370 --> 00:20:07.820 align:middle line:90%
He took it for six months.

00:20:07.820 --> 00:20:10.910 align:middle line:84%
It didn't really make any
difference to his cholesterol.

00:20:10.910 --> 00:20:14.440 align:middle line:84%
He just had side
effects, so he stopped

00:20:14.440 --> 00:20:16.480 align:middle line:90%
and rang the TV station.

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:17.770 align:middle line:90%
And I met him.

00:20:17.770 --> 00:20:19.720 align:middle line:90%
He was tired all the time.

00:20:19.720 --> 00:20:21.400 align:middle line:90%
He had five coffees a day.

00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:22.870 align:middle line:84%
In the evening,
he couldn't relax.

00:20:22.870 --> 00:20:27.610 align:middle line:84%
He didn't sleep so good, so he'd
have a beer, or maybe a wine.

00:20:27.610 --> 00:20:29.260 align:middle line:90%
And he was gaining weight.

00:20:29.260 --> 00:20:31.390 align:middle line:84%
And he wasn't doing
much exercise.

00:20:31.390 --> 00:20:33.160 align:middle line:90%
He just didn't have the energy.

00:20:33.160 --> 00:20:36.620 align:middle line:84%
So I told him what to do and
how to eat a low glycemic load

00:20:36.620 --> 00:20:37.420 align:middle line:90%
diet.

00:20:37.420 --> 00:20:42.460 align:middle line:84%
I gave him some supplements,
omega 3, niacin, vitamin B3,

00:20:42.460 --> 00:20:44.440 align:middle line:84%
which lowers cholesterol
incredibly well.

00:20:44.440 --> 00:20:45.290 align:middle line:90%


00:20:45.290 --> 00:20:49.000 align:middle line:84%
And what happened was that his
energy went through the roof.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:50.395 align:middle line:84%
When I met him
three weeks later,

00:20:50.395 --> 00:20:53.110 align:middle line:84%
his cholesterol had
completely normalized.

00:20:53.110 --> 00:20:57.760 align:middle line:84%
He'd lost 11 pounds, about
five kilos in weight,

00:20:57.760 --> 00:20:59.560 align:middle line:90%
really without trying.

00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:01.215 align:middle line:90%
And I said, how's the coffee?

00:21:01.215 --> 00:21:02.840 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I haven't
been having any.

00:21:02.840 --> 00:21:04.990 align:middle line:90%
My energy's been amazing.

00:21:04.990 --> 00:21:07.130 align:middle line:84%
And this is really
a key by the way,

00:21:07.130 --> 00:21:09.310 align:middle line:84%
is that most people say
they don't exercise,

00:21:09.310 --> 00:21:11.440 align:middle line:84%
because they haven't
got enough energy.

00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:14.020 align:middle line:84%
He said, I've started playing
football again, simply

00:21:14.020 --> 00:21:16.930 align:middle line:84%
because I've got
the energy to do it.

00:21:16.930 --> 00:21:19.060 align:middle line:90%
And I said, how's the sleeping?

00:21:19.060 --> 00:21:21.070 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh, I'm
sleeping like a baby.

00:21:21.070 --> 00:21:23.170 align:middle line:84%
